                    EARTH SCIENCE > ATMOSPHERE > ATMOSPHERIC TEMPERATURE > SURFACE AIR TEMPERATURE

                

                Definition:

                
                    In meteorology, the temperature of the ambient air near the surface of
the earth, almost invariably determined by a thermometer in an instrument
shelter. 

                

                
                    Reference:

                    
                        
                            
                                Glossary of Weather and Climate, American Meteorological Society, 1996. 
                            
                        

                    

                
            		
                
            
	
                
            				
                
            
			
                
            		



    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
        
    

    
